{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place water in mixing bowl and insert simmering basket. Weigh potatoes in simmering basket and cook <b>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula, transfer potatoes to a flat dish and allow to cool for approx. 30 minutes. Meanwhile, empty and dry mixing bowl and continue with recipe.","Place 20 g wheat grains in mixing bowl, crush <b>15 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place remaining 230 g wheat grains in mixing bowl, grind <b>1 min\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a separate bowl and set aside.","Place cooled potatoes and milk in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add yeast, 2 eggs, flour, salt, butter and ground wheat and knead <b>2 min\/<b> kneten. Transfer dough to a large bowl, cover with cling film or a damp kitchen towel and leave in a warm place for 30 minutes to rise until doubled in size.","Line a baking tray with baking paper. With floured hands, shape 6 equally-sized balls from the dough and place on baking tray. Cover bread rolls with cling film or a damp kitchen towel and leave in a warm place for approx. 45 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 200°C.","Whisk 1 egg and glaze the rolls, sprinkle with shredded wheat and bake in oven for 18–20 minutes (200°C) until golden. Allow to cool for 10 minutes and serve as desired."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["500 g water","250 g waxy potatoes, diced (1 cm) (see tip)","250 g wheat grains","75 g milk","1 cube fresh yeast (40 g)","3 eggs","250 g plain flour","2 tsp fine salt","60 g butter, soft, in pieces"]}],"id":"r126622","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-KI6JMF97o5U\/XZavHA0ruMI\/AAAAAAAAhrk\/i1Dm2JD-67owT5045nfpUqrDmkcBn39ugCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_h723yUjlbz3H1iRI.png","title":"Wholegrain hamburger buns","publishedAt":"2017-08-07T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"15 g","fat":"13 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"63 g","calories":"1837 kJ \/ 439 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray, baking paper, bowl, cling film or tea towel, large bowl, oven","hintsAndTricks":["In <b>step 5<b>, <b>250 g cooked potatoes<b> from the previous day, cut into pieces, can alternatively be used. The cooking and cooling described in <b>step 1<b> is then no longer necessary.","If the dough is very sticky after <b>step 5<b>, add <b>30 g flour<b> and knead another <strong>15 sec\/<\/strong>.","These bread rolls make ideal burger buns but are also perfect for breakfast or as a savoury snack."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","2h 50m","6 pieces"]}